<item>
            <title>[DERBY-3884] dblook scripts will fail to correctly recreate objects which depend on creator privileges</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3884</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The dblook utility produces a script which can be used to recreate the schema of a database. Permissions are added in one big block at the end of this script. However, the faithful recreation of some objects (like views) may depend on the creator being a specific user having specific privileges. Faithfully recreating the schema may require the ability to change user and sort, by dependency, the statements which dblook emits--so that  permission grants may be interleaved with object declarations. For a discussion of this problem, please see the commentary by Dag, dated 25/Sep/08, on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3877&quot; title=&quot;SQL roles: build support for dblook&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-3877&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-3877&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This problem was introduced when we added GRANT/REVOKE to Derby. The addition of SQL Roles creates more problem cases.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
